citeinfo.title: GISDevServices.DSGDO.pdsCosaBoundary

descript.abstract: This is a graphical polygon dataset depicting the polygon boundaries of the City of San Antonio
descript.purpose: The City of San Antonio dataset defines the area of one of the Cities within Bexar County, Texas and provides a representation of such polygons for the purpose of portraying the attributes for the county.
descript.supplinf: This metadata describes the dataset for the City of San Antonio, Texas, which is how the dataset was named on the City of San Antonio's Planning GIS. According to fields notes the square mile is 467.9 that fall within the San Antonio city limits, this includes the surrounding cities within San Antonio, (Castle Hills, Terrell Hill, Olmos Park, Alamo Heights, Hill Country Village, Hollywood Park). Without the Cities and Lackland AFB, within San Antonio the total would reflect approximately 466.6 square miles. Last updated on 09/30/2009; ordinance #2009-06-18-0516
